All across the United States, governments are using eminent domain proceedings in order to convert private land to what it sees as a higher civic purpose, like an industrial or commercial development. Here is a Google map mash-up put together by activists trying to fight the Supreme Court decision under Kelo v. City of New London that upheld the practice.

It shows the various controversies across the country. If you click on the pushpin you get the activists’ take on the local issue. — DAMON DARLIN